HEADWORD: Ascians
<hw>As"cians</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>ascii</ets>, pl.
of <ets>ascius</ets>, Gr. <?/ without shadow; <grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/
shadow.]</ety> <def>Persons who, at certain times of the year, have no
shadow at noon; -- applied to the inhabitants of the torrid zone, who
have, twice a year, a vertical sun.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

